doc.after: Like Cape Cod itself the islands south of the Cape have evolved from whaling and trading areas to become resort destinations attracting wealthy families celebrities and other tourists These include the large nearby islands of Martha s Vineyard and Nantucket which are themselves famous summer tourist destinations commonly accessed by ferry from Cape Cod The phrases Cape Cod and the Islands and the Cape and Islands are often used to describe the whole region of Barnstable County Dukes County including the Vineyard and the smaller Elizabeth Islands and Nantucket County
